  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Bilateral laryngeal reinnervation induces a rise in laryngeal resistance and speech
      alteration. The aim of this study is to propose laryngeal reinnervation by a phrenic nerve
      root to patients with bilateral laryngeal paralysis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
